SKILL|yvon-engine|"Build and maintain the YVON Engine standalone npm package (@yvon/engine). Covers: extracting CIE+TOON+agents from YVON monolith into an installable package, auto-init CLI pattern (yvon init for new projects, yvon integrate for existing projects), built-in knowledge graph builder, dashboard server, Hermes CRDT sync, code-review-graph MCP integration, npm packaging pitfalls, and the 'one command activates everything' user expectation."
STEP|1|CIE: Context Intelligence Engine (classify → retrieve → rank → inject)
STEP|2|TOON: Token-Optimized Object Notation (84.5% token savings on data tasks)
STEP|3|13 AI agents with full folder structures (AGENT.md, MEMORY.md, SESSION.md, SKILLS.md, skills/)
STEP|4|Built-in knowledge graph builder (JS/TS/Python import scanner)
STEP|5|Dashboard server (D3.js force graph, CIE pipeline, agent cards, token gauge)
STEP|6|Hermes CRDT bidirectional memory sync
STEP|7|code-review-graph MCP client (auto-detect, pip install suggestion)
STEP|8|Auto-detect existing features (graphify, codegraph, hermes, claude, nextjs, typescript)
STEP|9|Create missing project structure (CLAUDE.md, graph placeholders, venture docs, agent-memory/)
STEP|10|Deploy all 13 agents with full folder structures (803 template files)
STEP|11|Build knowledge graphs immediately (no external deps needed)
STEP|12|Write yvon.config.json with all paths configured
STEP|13|Show what was created, what was kept, and what optional deps to install
STEP|14|Never** require the user to run separate install commands for components that can be built-in. Graphify and codegraph are built-in. Only Hermes and Claude are external services (optional).
STEP|15|Arrow function array destructuring in forEach: `([a, b]) =>` — breaks in some Node versions
STEP|16|TypeScript type annotations: `function foo(p: string)` — breaks in plain JS
STEP|17|`Array.prototype.findLast` — not available in Node <18
STEP|18|Detect existing features (fs.existsSync checks)
STEP|19|Show what's found and what's missing
STEP|20|Create missing project structure
STEP|21|Deploy agent templates (only create if not existing)
STEP|22|Build knowledge graphs (inline builder, zero deps)
STEP|23|Write yvon.config.json
STEP|24|Show summary: created X, kept Y, optional deps
STEP|25|Rule:** Never overwrite existing files. Never require the user to run separate install commands for built-in features.
STEP|26|Scans project for `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.js`, `.jsx`, `.py` files
STEP|27|Extracts imports using regex patterns
STEP|28|Builds dependency graph with hub files (most imported) and high fan-out files
STEP|29|Generates GRAPH_REPORT.md and CODEGRAPH_REPORT.md
STEP|30|Skipped directories: `node_modules`, `.git`, `dist`, `.next`, `__pycache__`
STEP|31|Force-directed D3.js graph of codebase structure
STEP|32|CIE pipeline status panel (classified → retrieved → injected → filtered)
STEP|33|Agent status cards (13 agents with roles, models, status dots)
STEP|34|Token savings gauge (animated SVG arc at 84.5%)
STEP|35|Single self-contained HTML with inline CSS/JS — dark theme, glass-morphism
STEP|36|API endpoints: `/api/graph`, `/api/cie-status`, `/api/agents`, `/api/token-savings`
STEP|37|Exported as `startDashboard` from main `@yvon/engine` (added to exports field: `"./dashboard": "./dist/dashboard/index.js"`)
STEP|38|CLI command:** `npx yvon dashboard` — starts server on port 4200.
STEP|39|Dashboard v1 (current):** Single inline HTML page with static D3 graph, hardcoded CIE stats, token gauge at 84%. Serves as proof-of-concept.
STEP|40|Dashboard v2 (planned):** Full React SPA with Express API + WebSocket. See detailed plan at `.hermes/plans/2026-06-12_dashboard-v2-plan.md`. Key upgrades: live TOON metrics (actual tokens/cost saved),
